<org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmi:id="-7oQTzt79Gjlf1rRBE2xbDQ" name=",_xHpJgL-PEd2e1-cAeXIm5A" guid="-7oQTzt79Gjlf1rRBE2xbDQ" changeDate="2008-12-01T11:07:33.169+0100">
  <mainDescription>&lt;P class=MsoNormal style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN style=&quot;mso-ansi-language: EN-US&quot;>&lt;FONT size=3>&lt;FONT face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;>Analysis of the alternatives is an important task to take the best decision when selecting the architecture. It depends mainly on the policies defined to analyse the architectures proposed in the previous task and it is going to help developers to decide which architecture fits better with the problem. After this task, developers will obtain enhanced and improved architectural options, patterns and policies, which will help to take better decisions. &lt;?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = &quot;urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office&quot; />&lt;o:p>&lt;/o:p>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P></mainDescription>
  <sections xmi:id="_UBUgOMHrEd2B2LAvnwDruw" name="Define how to measure the architectures " guid="_UBUgOMHrEd2B2LAvnwDruw">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;span style=&quot;mso-ansi-language: EN-US&quot;>&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;>&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;>The first step is to establish all&#xD;
    the criteria to analyse the feasibility of each alternative. It is necessary to define what to measure and how to&#xD;
    measure it. Have in mind always enterprise strategies and policies (some measures could be given by enterprise policies&#xD;
    to guarantee a minimum QoS level).&lt;/font>&lt;/font>&lt;/span>&#xD;
&lt;/p></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_UBUgOsHrEd2B2LAvnwDruw" name="Perform assessment according to the defined criteria " guid="_UBUgOsHrEd2B2LAvnwDruw">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;P class=MsoNormal style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN style=&quot;mso-ansi-language: EN-US&quot;>&lt;FONT size=3>&lt;FONT face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;>Carry out the assessment and analysis of each option identified in the previous task. If some alternatives obtain very bad qualifications, they could be removed before ending the analysis. If this last approach is going to be taken, a limit score has to be defined for that purpose. That score will determine whether a solution is feasible from the enterprise strategic point of view. &lt;?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = &quot;urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office&quot; />&lt;o:p>&lt;/o:p>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P>&lt;SPAN style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA&quot;>It is possible to use SQUASH technique to carry out this task having in mind possible scenarios to solve the problem. To use this technique, different application scenarios should be defined in previous tasks. The usage of this technique could also determine the way to arrange ERA and ESA data&lt;/SPAN></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_UBUgOcHrEd2B2LAvnwDruw" name="Integrate results with previous ones " guid="_UBUgOcHrEd2B2LAvnwDruw">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;P class=MsoNormal style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN style=&quot;mso-ansi-language: EN-US&quot;>&lt;FONT size=3>&lt;FONT face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;>Finally, add the results to each architectural option data. This way, architectural options, patterns and policies will be completed with analysis data. &lt;?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = &quot;urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office&quot; />&lt;o:p>&lt;/o:p>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <purpose>&lt;span&#xD;
style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA&quot;>The&#xD;
purpose is to take the best decision when selecting the architecture&lt;/span></purpose>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
